      "text": "It is widely recognised that there is a need to integrate both [[Explicit Knowledge]] and [[Tacit Knowledge]] into a formal information system, a knowledge management system (KMS) comprising the creation or acquisition (generation of new insights, ideas, or routines), encapsulation, refinement, storage, management and dissemination of knowledge (Turban et al., 2008; Georgiadou and Siakas, 2011)."
